question: 新婚旅行
sourceMnemonic: You know that <ja>旅行</ja> is a <kanji>trip</kanji>. The other part is <kanji>new</kanji> <kanji>marriage</kanji>. What's the trip you go on after a new marriage? The <vocabulary>honeymoon</vocabulary>!
sourceReadingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word, which usually means on'yomi readings from the kanji. If you know the readings of your kanji you'll know how to read this as well.
